"title": "5376: law, purpose of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5376: law, purpose of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The law covers and regulates every area of life of the covenant people of God in accordance with the commands of God. Although the laws may be divided into categories of civil, criminal, social and cultic (or ritual) law, these distinctions are not clear-cut, and occasionally overlap with one another.</p>\n<h2>The origins of the law</h2>\n<h3>Law as God's command is found in the story of creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:16-Gen2:17\">GEN 2:16–2:17</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The law expresses the covenant relation between God and his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:44-Deut4:45\">DEU 4:44–4:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:1\">DEU 5:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:1-Exod20:17\">EXO 20:1–20:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:6-Deut5:21\">DEU 5:6–5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:12-Deut10:13\">DEU 10:12–10:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut30:1-Deut30:16\">DEU 30:1–30:16</a></p>\n<h2>The purpose of the law</h2>\n<h3>The law shows the proper response to the holiness of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:2\">LEV 19:2</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The law ensures that the people continue to receive the blessings of the covenant promises</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:24-Deut6:25\">DEU 6:24–6:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:17-Gen22:18\">GEN 22:17–22:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:12\">EXO 20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:3-Deut6:7\">DEU 6:3–6:7</a></p>\n<h3>Breaking the law leads to forfeiting the covenant blessings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:9-Jer11:11\">JER 11:9–11:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:1-Exod32:4\">EXO 32:1–32:4</a></p>\n<h3>The law deepens the believer's knowledge of God through meditation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:1-Ps1:2\">PSA 1:1–1:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:2\">DEU 6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:7-Ps19:14\">PSA 19:7–19:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:25-Ps119:32\">PSA 119:25–119:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:105-Ps119:120\">PSA 119:105–119:120</a></p>\n<h3>The law will finally be written on believers' hearts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:33\">JER 31:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:19-Ezek11:20\">EZK 11:19–11:20</a></p>\n<h2>The general principles underlying the law</h2>\n<h3>Justice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:20\">DEU 16:20</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Righteousness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:18\">DEU 16:18</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Holiness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:2\">LEV 19:2</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Love</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:18-Lev19:19\">LEV 19:18–19:19</a></strong></p>",
